Hi Jordan,

Thanks for reaching out. I checked your account and found that the password reset email had triggered a security hold because your account has multi-factor authentication (MFA) enabled via an authenticator app, and the reset flow requires re-confirming the MFA device. This is a known edge case when the MFA device was replaced recently.

I've manually cleared the security hold and sent a fresh password reset link that will skip the MFA re-confirmation step this one time. Please reset your password again using the new link, and then re-register your authenticator app under Account Settings > Security to avoid this happening again.

This aligns with the authentication requirements described in our Access Control Policy for customer-facing accounts with MFA enabled.

Let us know if you're still blocked after resetting.

Best,
Priya
Nimbus Analytics Support

